column19: Number of infected people was calculated by multiplying relevant population w the adjusted estimate of seroprevalence (or unadjusted if adjusted not available) - the analysis with maximal adjustment was selected. The number of deaths recorded at the time chosen by the authors of each study was selected - if no selection, number of deaths accumulated until after 1 week of mid-point of study period selcted. Inferred IFR was then obtained by dividing number of deaths by the number of infected people for the entire population and separately for people <70 years old. Values corrected for type of seroprevalence study performed (IgG, IgA, IgE, IgM)
